author: rwesten
msg: resolves STANBOL-37: The LocationEnhancement Engine can now use together with geonames.org user accounts
Added a readme for this engine  (based on the documentation found on the IKS wiki)
Added a description on how to setup free user accounts
Corrected several bugs related to cases where the default values where used even if others where parsed by the configuration.
The unit tests still use the ws.geonames.org (that does not require user authentication) because sharing a user account for testing reasons seamed not the right thing to do.
Also kept the default for the geonames server (http://ws.geonames.org) because changing it to http://api.geonames.org would require to create an user account.
updated the metatype properties to point users to the possibility to use http://api.geonames.org
